  "summary": "\u003cp\u003eI've enhanced Neovim's character navigation motions (\u003ccode\u003ef\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eF\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003et\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eT\u003c/code\u003e) by\nintegrating them with \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/smoka7/hop.nvim\"\u003ehop.nvim\u003c/a\u003e. The\ndefault behavior remains unchanged when there's only one occurrence of the\ntarget character, or when using a count prefix (like \u003ccode\u003e3f\u003c/code\u003e). However, when\nmultiple matches exist, hop.nvim automatically labels each occurrence, making\nit much easier to jump directly to your desired location.\u003c/p\u003e\n",
